WEBVTT

00:00:13.010 --> 00:00:13.990
Go!

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:00:24.980 --> 00:00:26.390
Whoa, this is...

00:00:26.390 --> 00:00:27.770
She's rustier than I thought.

00:00:37.660 --> 00:00:40.030
Teio, stay focused until you finish!

00:00:44.790 --> 00:00:47.260
What do you think, Trainer?

00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:49.830
She's still got a lot of work to do.

00:00:49.830 --> 00:00:50.800
That said...

00:00:52.800 --> 00:00:57.220
I'm happy enough that she's running again.

00:01:14.530 --> 00:01:21.740
Umamusume

00:01:17.700 --> 00:01:21.740
Pretty Derby

00:02:28.380 --> 00:02:30.390
Teio, here's your regimen.

00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:33.230
{\an1}Episode 11
 What I Feel

00:02:30.660 --> 00:02:34.820
Oof! Basic training, basic training, 
and more basic training...

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
Tokai Teio 
Special Training Plan!

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Stretching  30 Minutes

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Roadwork  1 Hour

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Rest  15 Minutes

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Ladder Training  20 Sets

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Strength Training  (Push-Ups, Midsection, Back)

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Rest  15 Minutes

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Tire Pulling 15

00:02:33.230 --> 00:02:36.730
• Curls  30 x 6 sets

00:02:34.820 --> 00:02:36.730
It's like I'm getting ready to debut again.

00:02:36.730 --> 00:02:39.850
I'm honestly kind of at 
a loss about what to do.

00:02:39.850 --> 00:02:41.410
But it's times like that—

00:02:41.410 --> 00:02:43.120
—you need to focus on the basics.

00:02:43.120 --> 00:02:46.370
I'm gonna work hard, like I'm 
starting over from scratch.

00:02:46.740 --> 00:02:47.620
Teio...

00:02:47.620 --> 00:02:51.910
Plus, I'm already enjoying just 
being able to run on the track again.

00:02:52.350 --> 00:02:54.500
Yeah. Let's work hard together.

00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:55.880
Gotta say, though...

00:02:56.220 --> 00:02:58.220
This place is a mess!

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:01.390
I've been kind of pressed for time lately.

00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:05.140
Been trying to keep track of the other 
teams, and their noteworthy runners.

00:03:05.390 --> 00:03:08.680
A lot of them have grown
a bunch over the summer.

00:03:09.140 --> 00:03:11.980
Do you think I can help?

00:03:11.980 --> 00:03:12.890
Say what?

00:03:12.890 --> 00:03:14.210
It's for the team's sake, right?

00:03:14.210 --> 00:03:17.400
I wanna do what I can to pay 
the others back for their help.

00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:20.400
Still, I'm not sure I should—

00:03:21.150 --> 00:03:23.570
It'll be fine, just leave it to me!

00:03:23.570 --> 00:03:25.970
I've got a knack for surveillance!

00:03:37.420 --> 00:03:38.500
That's so weird.

00:03:37.790 --> 00:03:39.420
Target confirmed.

00:03:38.500 --> 00:03:39.810
What the heck?

00:03:39.810 --> 00:03:42.800
So my grandma couldn't 
find her dentures, right?

00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:45.410
Winning Ticket...

00:03:43.880 --> 00:03:49.270
Notable Accomplishments

00:03:44.800 --> 00:03:50.140
• Yayoishou (GII)

00:03:45.410 --> 00:03:47.790
Said to be among the three strongest 
horse girls of the new generation,

00:03:46.140 --> 00:03:51.060
1st Place

00:03:46.640 --> 00:03:51.060
• Satsuki Sho (GI)

00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:51.060
along with Biwa Hayahide 
and Narita Taishin...

00:03:47.970 --> 00:03:51.060
4th place

00:03:48.470 --> 00:03:51.060
• Tokyo Derby (GI)

00:03:49.810 --> 00:03:51.060
1st Place

00:03:51.370 --> 00:03:52.940
After losing in the Satsuki Sho,

00:03:52.940 --> 00:03:55.810
she took the Derby while 
also being ranked most popular.

00:03:55.810 --> 00:03:59.250
She shows excellent acceleration in the
way she moves up during the final stretch.

00:03:59.250 --> 00:04:02.820
and her preparations for the Kikkashou 
are looking pitch-perfect.

00:04:02.820 --> 00:04:06.260
Lives by the motto, "Be a powerful lady."

00:04:06.260 --> 00:04:07.200
Okay!

00:04:08.530 --> 00:04:10.100
What is she doing?

00:04:10.100 --> 00:04:11.290
She's crawling somewhere!

00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:19.720
Let's see...

00:04:18.440 --> 00:04:20.550
The Runaway

00:04:21.250 --> 00:04:22.640
Mejiro Palmer.

00:04:21.590 --> 00:04:26.930
{\an7}Notable Accomplishments
 • Takarazuka Kinen (G1)
      1st Place
  • Arima Kinen (GI)
       1st Place
  • Hanshin Daishoten (GII)
       2nd Place
  • Tennoushou (Spring) (GI)
       3rd Place

00:04:22.640 --> 00:04:24.380
Managed to win both Grand Prix races,

00:04:24.380 --> 00:04:26.930
the Takarazuka Kinen and 
Arima Kinen, last year.

00:04:26.930 --> 00:04:30.990
Accelerates to full speed early on, 
and at this year's Spring Tennoushou,

00:04:30.990 --> 00:04:33.840
she was able to take the lead early, 
then finish in third place.

00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:37.490
She sets a crazy pace for everyone else, 
making her a tough cookie to race against.

00:04:37.490 --> 00:04:42.090
Sucks at hurdle races, and comes 
back from them all banged up.

00:04:42.090 --> 00:04:43.240
Okay!

00:04:46.240 --> 00:04:49.030
What is that girl even doing?

00:04:49.030 --> 00:04:50.370
Is something the matter, President?

00:04:50.650 --> 00:04:52.240
No, not really.

00:04:52.240 --> 00:04:54.360
I need you to sign off on these.

00:04:54.360 --> 00:04:55.500
Right.

00:04:59.840 --> 00:05:01.250
Here we go...

00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:03.150
Rice Shower.

00:05:02.170 --> 00:05:06.970
Notable Accomplishments

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:07.630
• Tokyo Derby (GI)

00:05:03.150 --> 00:05:05.510
After thwarting Mihono 
Bourbon's Triple Crown,

00:05:03.380 --> 00:05:08.180
2nd Place

00:05:04.170 --> 00:05:08.760
• Kikkasho (GI)

00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:08.760
1st Place

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:08.760
• Nikkei Sho (GII)

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:09.190
she ended Mejiro McQueen's winning 
streak at the Spring Tennoushou,

00:05:06.050 --> 00:05:08.760
1st Place

00:05:06.840 --> 00:05:08.760
• Tennoushou (Spring) (GI)

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:08.760
1st place

00:05:09.190 --> 00:05:11.890
demonstrating her strength as a stayer.

00:05:12.390 --> 00:05:16.170
She was really amazing 
at the Spring Tennoushou!

00:05:16.170 --> 00:05:20.110
Oh, I should make a note that 
she eats bread with breakfast.

00:05:20.110 --> 00:05:21.150
There we go!

00:05:23.650 --> 00:05:27.400
I checked her out already, 
and this one is done, too.

00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:29.780
Let's see, let's grab a Shaky-Shaky Jelly,

00:05:29.780 --> 00:05:32.390
the kind that you're supposed 
to shake a bunch...

00:05:38.740 --> 00:05:40.290
What the heck?!

00:05:41.020 --> 00:05:43.980
I ended up accidentally getting the 
1.5 liter soda bottle instead of

00:05:43.980 --> 00:05:47.150
the 150 milliliter Shaky-Shaky Jelly!

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:50.060
Tokai Teio...

00:05:54.780 --> 00:05:56.120
Biwa Hayahide!

00:05:56.560 --> 00:05:59.490
She's been in first or second 
place in every race she's run in.

00:05:59.490 --> 00:06:02.060
One of the famous BNW trio.

00:06:02.060 --> 00:06:03.740
I can't!

00:06:02.460 --> 00:06:05.150
The way she leaves the competition 
behind during straightaways

00:06:05.150 --> 00:06:07.070
gives her a real champion's aura.

00:06:07.870 --> 00:06:09.190
And I have to wonder...

00:06:10.050 --> 00:06:12.840
Why is she so intimidating?

00:06:15.540 --> 00:06:17.250
Decarbonated cola, eh?

00:06:18.070 --> 00:06:19.500
Very impressive.

00:06:20.710 --> 00:06:26.120
From the data I've seen, flat soda has 
an incredibly high energy efficiency,

00:06:26.120 --> 00:06:29.450
to the point that marathon runners have 
been known to drink it before a race.

00:06:29.450 --> 00:06:32.220
I would expect nothing less from Tokai Teio.

00:06:32.220 --> 00:06:33.530
Uh, I really just...

00:06:33.530 --> 00:06:35.220
No need to be modest.

00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:39.610
You've got a perfect grasp of nutritional 
theory in addition to your athletic ability.

00:06:39.610 --> 00:06:42.810
I can see why you were once 
known as the greatest.

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:44.610
Sis...

00:06:44.610 --> 00:06:46.230
Yes, I know.

00:06:46.230 --> 00:06:47.760
My apologies for the interruption.

00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:51.700
Should we ever race each other, 
try not to be too hard on me.

00:06:51.700 --> 00:06:53.710
Never thought you knew Tokai Teio.

00:06:53.710 --> 00:06:55.770
Guess everybody knows your face, Sis.

00:06:55.770 --> 00:06:57.630
Are you saying my face is big?!

00:07:00.470 --> 00:07:01.710
Machikane Tannhäuser.

00:07:02.060 --> 00:07:04.740
Has plenty of stamina, 
and a knack for long distances.

00:07:04.740 --> 00:07:08.630
Managed to beat Rice Shower 
at this year's Meguro Kinen.

00:07:11.110 --> 00:07:12.430
Nice Nature.

00:07:12.430 --> 00:07:15.350
Came in third place at the Arima 
Kinen for two years in a row.

00:07:15.350 --> 00:07:17.770
Despite having difficulty 
managing to secure wins,

00:07:17.770 --> 00:07:21.310
her reliable running means she's 
consistently on the scoreboard at the end of—

00:07:21.620 --> 00:07:22.810
Teio?

00:07:23.590 --> 00:07:25.740
Why are you wearing that?

00:07:25.740 --> 00:07:27.550
Well, it's...

00:07:29.070 --> 00:07:32.900
You can spy all you want, but try 
to stay out of the way, okay?

00:07:32.900 --> 00:07:33.700
You knew?!

00:07:33.950 --> 00:07:36.190
It was kind of obvious in that getup.

00:07:37.230 --> 00:07:39.830
Don't just goof off, okay? 
You need to train, too.

00:07:39.830 --> 00:07:41.580
I know!

00:07:41.840 --> 00:07:45.660
I'm looking forward to seeing 
you race again, too, y'know.

00:07:45.660 --> 00:07:47.340
Y-You are?

00:07:48.550 --> 00:07:51.710
I've had such a hard time 
winning anything lately.

00:07:52.330 --> 00:07:57.470
I mean, I know that I'm not 
really amazing or anything.

00:07:57.740 --> 00:08:02.020
But just when I think, 
"Maybe next time," I end up injured.

00:08:02.020 --> 00:08:07.820
To be honest, I was on the verge of giving 
up when I heard you'd be running again.

00:08:08.660 --> 00:08:14.450
And when I saw you refuse to give up, 
it made me think I shouldn't, either.

00:08:15.050 --> 00:08:16.450
Nature...

00:08:16.450 --> 00:08:19.680
Gosh, what am I getting so sentimental about?

00:08:19.680 --> 00:08:21.130
Talk about embarrassing!

00:08:21.550 --> 00:08:22.830
Forget I said anything, okay?!

00:08:23.390 --> 00:08:26.460
I'm only back because of everyone else.

00:08:26.830 --> 00:08:29.850
A lot of people have managed 
to show me how they feel.

00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:36.850
Well, be sure to tell them how <i>you</i> feel.

00:08:36.850 --> 00:08:38.600
Just like I did, okay?

00:08:39.050 --> 00:08:40.700
Thanks again, Teio!

00:08:42.210 --> 00:08:44.120
Thanks, huh...

00:08:45.350 --> 00:08:48.230
Turbo, Turbo, Turbo!

00:08:48.230 --> 00:08:51.760
If you think you can beat Turbo...

00:08:53.360 --> 00:08:54.840
Tokai Teio!

00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:56.100
Hey, race me!

00:08:56.100 --> 00:08:56.990
Maybe next time,

00:08:56.990 --> 00:08:58.740
Master Twin Turbo!

00:09:00.010 --> 00:09:01.750
She remembered my name.

00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:03.360
Wait, Master?

00:09:06.140 --> 00:09:08.860
Be sure to tell them how </i>you<i> feel.

00:09:10.370 --> 00:09:12.260
Thank you! Thank you!

00:09:14.010 --> 00:09:15.280
Here I am!

00:09:14.010 --> 00:09:17.260
Spica

00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:17.260
And I got plenty of candid shots.

00:09:17.260 --> 00:09:19.180
Let's take a look...

00:09:19.760 --> 00:09:21.490
Horse girl registered with Team Canopus.
Placed third place two years in a row at
the Arima Kinen. Has had trouble winning
a race in the GI, but her reliable racing
 consistently puts her onto the scoreboard,
and can't be underestimated. Has the most
 common sense of anyone on Canopus.

00:09:19.760 --> 00:09:21.490
Avec Dream
Not many notable accomplishments
after debut at the Twinkle Series,
but after switching her style up,
 at the Kinshachisho (GII)....

00:09:21.490 --> 00:09:23.930
Machikane Tannhäuser
A horse girl who specializes in middle
and long distance races affiliated with
Team Canopus. Has yet to win a GI race
but came in third place at the Kikkasho (GI).
Has previously won against the 
Kikkashou-winning Rice Shower.

00:09:21.490 --> 00:09:23.930
Rice Shower
Known as the Ebon Stayer. Has won,
and even set records at,
long-distance races like 
the Kikkashou (GI) and Tennoushou (GI)...

00:09:22.160 --> 00:09:23.930
These are... candid?

00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:25.390
Hey, Trainer.

00:09:26.340 --> 00:09:27.330
Thanks.

00:09:28.190 --> 00:09:30.050
Whoa, what got into you?

00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:32.780
You're the one helping me. I oughta—

00:09:32.780 --> 00:09:34.330
It's how I feel about all your help.

00:09:34.330 --> 00:09:36.070
Let's keep working hard together!

00:09:36.790 --> 00:09:38.890
Yeah, you bet.

00:09:39.950 --> 00:09:41.140
Teio?

00:09:41.140 --> 00:09:42.330
I see you're back.

00:09:43.160 --> 00:09:45.830
Excellent work on your mission, Teio-san!

00:09:50.810 --> 00:09:52.960
What's got you looking so serious?

00:09:53.430 --> 00:09:55.460
Guys... thank you.

00:09:55.730 --> 00:09:59.470
When I went up on stage... I was able to 
get over some things thanks to you all.

00:09:59.470 --> 00:10:00.950
Took you long enough—

00:10:01.670 --> 00:10:03.600
Thank you, Gold Ship.

00:10:03.600 --> 00:10:05.240
You too, Spe-chan.

00:10:05.240 --> 00:10:07.390
Oh, it was nothing!

00:10:07.390 --> 00:10:09.800
You too, Vodka, Scarlet.

00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:12.000
Well, when you go to the trouble 
of saying it out loud...

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:13.270
It's kind of embarrassing.

00:10:16.350 --> 00:10:18.390
That really hurt...

00:10:19.140 --> 00:10:22.360
Okay! That just leaves McQueen!

00:10:26.160 --> 00:10:29.290
McQueen! Hey!

00:10:29.290 --> 00:10:30.940
Teio?

00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:32.890
Working late, I see!

00:10:32.890 --> 00:10:34.290
Did you need something?

00:10:34.290 --> 00:10:36.920
I just wanted to talk to you.

00:10:38.690 --> 00:10:39.950
I understand.

00:10:41.560 --> 00:10:43.430
You were a spy?

00:10:43.430 --> 00:10:45.060
I sure was!

00:10:45.060 --> 00:10:47.180
I was all lurking in the shadows and stuff!

00:10:47.810 --> 00:10:49.960
I would've liked to have seen that.

00:10:49.960 --> 00:10:52.540
Also, there's something else, McQueen...

00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:54.280
What is it?

00:10:54.280 --> 00:10:57.100
For the other day... or really, 
more like, all the time...

00:10:58.190 --> 00:10:59.190
I wanted to say tha—

00:11:00.560 --> 00:11:01.700
Tha?

00:11:02.090 --> 00:11:02.910
Tha...

00:11:04.810 --> 00:11:07.450
Teio? Is something the matter?

00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:10.460
Huh. That's weird.

00:11:10.460 --> 00:11:14.930
Teio? "Tha" what, Teio?

00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:14.030
I was able to say it so 
easily to the others.

00:11:15.460 --> 00:11:17.020
Why not her?

00:11:15.870 --> 00:11:17.020
Teio?

00:11:20.650 --> 00:11:22.340
W-Well...

00:11:23.010 --> 00:11:24.340
Um...

00:11:26.350 --> 00:11:29.420
You're acting like someone 
about to confess their love.

00:11:29.420 --> 00:11:30.620
I am?!

00:11:31.230 --> 00:11:32.700
I'm joking, of course.

00:11:34.310 --> 00:11:37.730
U-Uh, I just remembered something I need to do!

00:11:37.730 --> 00:11:38.750
See ya!

00:11:38.750 --> 00:11:39.690
Teio?

00:11:39.690 --> 00:11:41.780
Argh, what is going on?!

00:11:41.780 --> 00:11:44.200
I just wanted to say thank you!

00:11:44.430 --> 00:11:48.030
What is wrong with me?!

00:11:48.030 --> 00:11:52.040
Umamusume

00:11:48.030 --> 00:11:52.040
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:11:55.130 --> 00:11:57.450
I didn't get any sleep last night.

00:11:57.450 --> 00:11:58.280
Teio?

00:11:59.050 --> 00:12:00.700
M-McQueen!

00:12:00.700 --> 00:12:04.050
What's the matter? You seem rather tired.

00:12:04.050 --> 00:12:06.690
I was up thinking last night.

00:12:06.690 --> 00:12:10.910
Is something bothering you? 
You've been acting strange since yesterday.

00:12:10.910 --> 00:12:12.710
Nothing, really!

00:12:15.470 --> 00:12:18.010
You don't seem to have a fever.

00:12:18.940 --> 00:12:22.690
O-Of course not! Why would I?!

00:12:23.920 --> 00:12:26.420
I'm just making this harder 
on myself by overthinking it.

00:12:26.420 --> 00:12:29.180
I just need to come out and say it! Normally!

00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:31.210
McQueen!

00:12:31.210 --> 00:12:32.080
Yes?

00:12:32.080 --> 00:12:34.230
Th-Tha... Tha...

00:12:34.230 --> 00:12:39.620
Uh, tha... than... um, tha...

00:12:39.620 --> 00:12:42.960
Oh, dear, that's the bell! We should hurry!

00:12:46.470 --> 00:12:48.470
• Arima Kinen

00:12:46.470 --> 00:12:48.470
• Takarazuka Kinen

00:12:46.470 --> 00:12:49.720
The two races where entrants are 
decided by popular ballot are the

00:12:49.720 --> 00:12:51.970
Takarazuka Kinen and Arima Kinen.

00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:51.420
Why her?

00:12:51.970 --> 00:12:55.940
Why is it that, with McQueen, I get so nervous?

00:12:55.190 --> 00:12:56.980
Twin Turbo-san!

00:12:56.980 --> 00:13:02.490
And she's the last member of 
Spica that I haven't thanked.

00:13:02.980 --> 00:13:04.410
At this rate...

00:13:05.010 --> 00:13:12.490
Thank you

00:13:07.180 --> 00:13:07.940
May I...

00:13:07.940 --> 00:13:08.550
Hell no.

00:13:08.550 --> 00:13:10.860
This thanks is for me.

00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:12.490
Could I...

00:13:12.490 --> 00:13:13.540
You can't have it.

00:13:14.260 --> 00:13:15.210
You can't have it!

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:19.710
Boo-hoo-hoo...

00:13:19.710 --> 00:13:22.330
You don't have to get so mad, Spe-chan!

00:13:22.330 --> 00:13:23.840
I don't have to what, now?

00:13:25.080 --> 00:13:26.980
Spe-chan!

00:13:28.610 --> 00:13:32.110
You're having trouble telling 
someone how you feel?

00:13:32.110 --> 00:13:35.120
I was wondering if there 
was a trick I could use.

00:13:35.120 --> 00:13:37.980
Good question. If it was me...

00:13:38.590 --> 00:13:41.600
I would put my feelings into a snack, 
using the language of snacks!

00:13:41.600 --> 00:13:43.090
There's a language of those?

00:13:43.090 --> 00:13:43.870
Yes!

00:13:43.870 --> 00:13:47.580
For example, baumkuchen represents 
a desire for continued happiness!

00:13:47.580 --> 00:13:50.000
Tiramisu is a way of asking 
for someone to cheer you up.

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:52.900
Carrot pancakes represent feeling full!

00:13:52.900 --> 00:13:55.380
Carrot-stuffed mochi represents free seconds.

00:13:55.380 --> 00:13:57.500
And this is something you learned, Spe-chan?

00:13:57.500 --> 00:13:59.620
I did! But opinions vary!

00:14:00.990 --> 00:14:03.850
I think the idea of a 
present might work, though.

00:14:07.670 --> 00:14:09.510
Look at this, Teio-san!

00:14:09.510 --> 00:14:12.500
It's a premium carrot with a honey glaze!

00:14:12.500 --> 00:14:14.890
I think this is supposed to represent...

00:14:14.930 --> 00:14:17.520
Carrot

00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:17.520
We're not shopping for you, Spe-chan!

00:14:19.010 --> 00:14:22.400
Would a snack really work, 
like Spe-chan thinks?

00:14:24.200 --> 00:14:25.400
Teio-san!

00:14:25.650 --> 00:14:28.900
Kita-chan? And Dia-chan's with you.

00:14:28.900 --> 00:14:31.920
Wait... huh? What's with the outfits?

00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:35.040
Trick or treat!

00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:36.710
Oh, Halloween!

00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:38.160
Yes, that's right!

00:14:38.160 --> 00:14:40.330
You better give us a treat...

00:14:40.330 --> 00:14:42.040
Or we'll play a trick on you!

00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:44.330
You two look so cute!

00:14:44.330 --> 00:14:45.560
Yay!

00:14:45.560 --> 00:14:46.910
Is it okay if I take a picture?

00:14:46.910 --> 00:14:47.880
Sure!

00:14:47.880 --> 00:14:48.800
Please!

00:14:49.150 --> 00:14:50.940
Let's see...

00:14:51.800 --> 00:14:53.510
Good Luck

00:14:53.510 --> 00:14:55.340
Okay, say cheeseburger!

00:14:56.760 --> 00:14:58.550
Teio-san, is that...

00:15:00.030 --> 00:15:03.660
I'm counting on the charm you made 
me to help keep me going, okay?

00:15:03.660 --> 00:15:06.870
Okay! I'll always be rooting for you!

00:15:06.870 --> 00:15:07.650
Right.

00:15:07.650 --> 00:15:09.380
And thanks again.

00:15:14.050 --> 00:15:17.410
Funny, I don't have any trouble 
saying it to Kita-chan.

00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:22.790
Well, I've been meaning to 
say thank you to McQueen,

00:15:22.790 --> 00:15:24.670
but it's been hard for some reason.

00:15:24.670 --> 00:15:26.100
Do you know what I mean?

00:15:26.580 --> 00:15:28.730
Can't you just tell her?

00:15:28.730 --> 00:15:31.260
Well, you're right, but...

00:15:31.260 --> 00:15:34.710
Okay, why don't you try 
saying it to Dia-chan?

00:15:34.710 --> 00:15:37.390
Just an "I appreciate everything 
you do for me" kind of thing.

00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:39.470
Oh, that'll be easy!

00:15:39.910 --> 00:15:41.140
This should be fun!

00:15:42.140 --> 00:15:43.480
Dia-chan!

00:15:43.480 --> 00:15:44.900
Yes, go ahead.

00:15:46.030 --> 00:15:47.030
Well...

00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:47.820
Yes?

00:15:50.280 --> 00:15:54.470
Um... thank you for always 
being with me and...

00:15:55.030 --> 00:15:56.120
Well...

00:15:57.280 --> 00:15:59.260
It's like you're confessing 
your love or something!

00:16:00.260 --> 00:16:02.210
You're blushing bright red, Kita-chan!

00:16:02.710 --> 00:16:05.670
Aw, quit teasing me!

00:16:05.670 --> 00:16:10.520
I guess the closer you are to someone, 
the more embarrassing it is.

00:16:10.520 --> 00:16:14.550
I always get embarrassed talking 
to my mom on Mother's Day.

00:16:15.300 --> 00:16:18.580
Kita-chan, what do you think about me?

00:16:18.580 --> 00:16:19.680
What do you mean?!

00:16:20.560 --> 00:16:23.380
You're my rival, and my best friend, and...

00:16:24.440 --> 00:16:26.190
I care about you a lot!

00:16:29.050 --> 00:16:32.870
Th-This is even more embarrassing, Kita-chan!

00:16:35.860 --> 00:16:36.840
I get it now.

00:16:38.190 --> 00:16:41.640
That's right. It's simpler than I figured.

00:16:42.580 --> 00:16:45.230
To me, McQueen is...

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.340
Mejiro McQueen-sama

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.340
This is an invitation to a date ♥

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.340
I'll be waiting for you in front 
 of Tracen Academy tomorrow at 11 AM!

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.340
Don't miss it!

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.340
From Tokai Teio

00:17:07.070 --> 00:17:08.610
Teio!

00:17:14.980 --> 00:17:19.430
I'm sorry, it took a moment 
to figure out this costume.

00:17:19.430 --> 00:17:22.260
And I've never worn it before, 
so I'm not sure about how it looks.

00:17:22.260 --> 00:17:23.450
It's okay!

00:17:23.450 --> 00:17:25.710
You look great!

00:17:26.850 --> 00:17:29.180
That's a relief to hear.

00:17:30.450 --> 00:17:33.380
All right, let's get this 
Halloween date on the road!

00:17:38.340 --> 00:17:40.850
Miyazaki-Sourced Chicken

00:17:38.340 --> 00:17:40.850
Takoyaki

00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:46.420
What brought this on all of a sudden?

00:17:46.420 --> 00:17:50.860
Well, I figured you'd like a celebration 
that involved a lot of sweets.

00:17:50.860 --> 00:17:52.540
D-Don't be ridiculous!

00:17:52.540 --> 00:17:54.690
I've actually been cutting back lately.

00:18:01.710 --> 00:18:03.990
I think they're selling crepes over there.

00:18:03.990 --> 00:18:05.350
They are?!

00:18:06.080 --> 00:18:08.060
I mean, clearly they are.

00:18:08.770 --> 00:18:11.640
Let's check everything out! Come on!

00:18:11.640 --> 00:18:12.880
Right.

00:18:15.380 --> 00:18:16.640
Here you are!

00:18:16.640 --> 00:18:18.880
Thank you!

00:18:17.380 --> 00:18:18.880
Ba<font color="#e57a9d">ll</font><font color="#f0d0a0">oo</font><font color="#ea718d">ns</font>

00:18:22.310 --> 00:18:23.890
You can do it, McQueen!

00:18:25.890 --> 00:18:27.890
Cotton Candy

00:18:30.520 --> 00:18:32.150
That's not how that works!

00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:37.400
I can't hit it...

00:18:37.890 --> 00:18:39.250
Leave it to me.

00:18:39.250 --> 00:18:40.320
Okay!

00:18:41.250 --> 00:18:42.740
That's not how that works.

00:18:44.240 --> 00:18:46.040
That is also not how that works.

